			<tr><td colspan="2">
				<div class="postbody">
				Ok, so I finished this game on Veteran. Heres what I think. 
<br />

<br />

<br />
Best single player game I have ever played. Hands down. The acting was great, the storyline straight out of one of those fabled "good" horror movies. The weapons very well done, the shotgun rocked especially. The progression of the game makes sense to the point where you don't spend for freaking ever trying to find out what the next little button to hit or secret room to find is, while still having plenty of secrets to find. 
<br />

<br />
Scary as hell. I physically jumped out of my chair at least 5 times while I was playing it. Some of the things that happen in this game are just wrong. Loved it. I'm actually playing through it again, and finding it to be fun even the second time around. 
<br />

<br />
All that said...
<br />

<br />
The multiplayer is indeed a big piece of @#%$. The server select is buggy as hell, the game lags to the point where its unfun with any more then 2 people playing it (which i think is why they limited it to 4). Its completely geared towards rocket whoring (which i despise) and running around and jumping like a fool at breakneck speed. (which i also despise)
<br />

<br />
Overall, worthwhile for anyone. Loved it loved it loved it, and I can even forgive the %@$# multiplayer.<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
				</div>
			</td></tr>
		</table>
		</td>
